RAICBICAICBICROC

# 
# pROCROC
if (!require(pROC)) install.packages("pROC") # pROC

library(pROC) # pROC

# datamodel

# AIC
step_aic <- step(model, direction = "both", k = 2) # AICk=2AIC
print("AIC:")
print(attr(summary(step_aic)$terms, "term.labels")) # AIC

# BIC
step_bic <- step(model, direction = "both", k = log(nrow(data))) # BICk=log(n)BIC
print("BIC:")
print(attr(summary(step_bic)$terms, "term.labels")) # BIC

# AICBIC
print("AIC:")
print(summary(step_aic))
print("BIC:")
print(summary(step_bic))

# 
pred_original <- predict(model, type="response")
pred_aic <- predict(step_aic, type="response")
pred_bic <- predict(step_bic, type="response")

# ROC
roc_original <- roc(data$status01, pred_original)
roc_aic <- roc(data$status01, pred_aic)
roc_bic <- roc(data$status01, pred_bic)

plot(roc_original, main=" vs AIC vs BIC ROC", col="red")
lines(roc_aic, col="blue")
lines(roc_bic, col="green")

legend("bottomright", legend=c("Original", "AIC", "BIC"), col=c("red", "blue", "green"), lty=1)
